  "description": "Details of surface water drainage scheme for Eastern access (Randolph Road rear access only) pursuant to condition 65 (partial) of planning permission reference PP/2015/4682 dated 18/02/2016 for Section 73 application for minor amendment to vary condition 3 to amend the outline scheme drawings pertaining to the 2010 masterplan in respect of outline approval for demolition of 22 house; the remediation of the land and the redevelopment of the site to deliver a large mixed use development including residential, non-food retail, food retail, restaurants, bars and cafes, hotel, conference and banqueting, cinema, health care facilities, education facilities, office/studio units, car parks, sports pavilion, an energy centre, multi-storey car park and associated car and cycle parking, landscaping, public realm, open space and children's play space. \nFull application: new access roads from Hayes-by-Pass and Southall town centre to the application site for vehicle, cycle and pedestrian access, including drainage and flood relief pond. Widening of South Road across the railway line, for the creation of a bus lane and thee new accesses onto Beaconsfield Road. Two bridges over the Grand Union Canal and Yeading Brook to provide pedestrian and cycle access to Minet Country park and Springfield Road application reference P/2008/3981-s dated 29 September 2010. The quantum of the development remains the same as the original scheme with the exception that the proposed development now includes a police facility and public toilets. in summary the proposed amendment to the scheme are: (1) re-distribution of public realm; (2) re-configuration of the internal street network; (3) re-positioning of the Civic Square; (4) re-locating the primary school; (5) improvement to the canal side; (6)re-configuration of buildings around the retained land; (7) alignment of western access on the gasworks site; (8) provision of commercial access",
